2026-03-29T16:33:14.5401924Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Adds a \"Download Sanitized Database\" button to the About page in the admin portal\r\n- Creates a consistent SQLite snapshot via VACUUM INTO, then strips sensitive fields (OAuth tokens, email addresses) before serving the file\r\n- Uses a SemaphoreSlim to prevent concurrent exports and cleans up temp files in a finally block\r\n- Follows existing DatabaseBackupService patterns for safe SQLite file operations\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Admin/Pages/About.cshtml.cs` — New `OnPostExportSanitizedDbAsync` handler with VACUUM INTO, sanitization UPDATEs, and file download\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Admin/Pages/About.cshtml` — Database Export section with download button and error display via TempData\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Admin.Tests/AboutModelTests.cs` — Updated constructor calls for new ILogger parameter; added CreateModel helper\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Admin.Tests/Integration/AboutPageTests.cs` — Integration test verifying the export button renders\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] All 565 existing + new tests pass (verified locally)\r\n- [ ] Navigate to About page and confirm \"Database Export\" section with download button appears\r\n- [ ] Click \"Download Sanitized Database\" and verify a .db file is downloaded\r\n- [ ] Open the downloaded .db and verify Hubs.AccessToken, Hubs.RefreshToken, Hubs.HueApplicationKey are empty and Customers.Email, CcEmails, BccEmails are empty\r\n- [ ] Verify non-sensitive data (devices, readings, polling logs) is preserved",
